(window.webpackJsonp=window.webpackJsonp||[]).push([[68],{204:function(e){e.exports={data:{post:{title:"Up, up, up! Down, down, down...",content:'<h3 id="2018-hasnt-been-a-very-progressive-year"><a href="#2018-hasnt-been-a-very-progressive-year" aria-hidden="true"><span class="icon icon-link"></span></a>2018 hasn’t been a very... progressive year.</h3>\n<p>After moving back from the city at the end of last year, my responsibilities and life have become rather static. I get told I do an important job and do it well, but I still feel sharply pathetic revealing what I do. Saying to someone that I look after an elderly man in a small, dead town isn’t very attractive.\n<a href="/assets/static/src/media/images/blog/AtTheBog.jpg"><img class="g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill=\'none\' viewBox=\'0 0 512 512\' xmlns=\'http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\' xmlns:xlink=\'http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id=\'__svg-blur-13\'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in=\'SourceGraphic\' stdDeviation=\'40\'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x=\'0\' y=\'0\' filter=\'url(%23__svg-blur-13)\' width=\'512\' height=\'512\' xlink:href=\'data:image/jpeg%3bbase64%%2blA4jo2EoOB1bNed4T0FMd4fhrwyH4KHQJ2sceRh4D60hpG8MfSkd6f7ZpJkPw4/OjURTnnk%2betnrsUYUTxkLjHutygeuPGpY4i5JA4aYe9zKy8o2H/utbVx7/T%2bl9dPecM3kUCsc9xKDgfI1lGtdkXFOmScr26yrnHOGBFeq5lh9PB%2b0FnCXbTrGmyRW093JcWCuAWuF71wvjynIJx5V0Pa6te3EEc0WpWskcihkYWzYIIyD96uTtU7Oruw4WlvWlxeQ/aFAdiviPnW0dk87y9nuivcThXMRGGVicBmA/SmK1sz%2brojWlJftmnrqt4gzJPE5/wAYmH/VJl1u9AzGobyyMfvQ9mMnPfyN/rD/ACadhEbH3vaseeFX%2baLdlD7%2byY/EGtmKbu4bV5gPsgSQCfHm8qi3HEXEYMogtYe8Cr3YKcwJx7xODnHkBTs8FusDSJG0oUZJaY5%2bgxVDLKkjjuFUN4HJ5h6jeo549kcteTQ1kIUYcN6ZqDrTBLUd8FOfBckn0ArK%2bFuONX1i89hTTGS4OSJIySgA9T40HcXcQcR3fEU1rFJNbLCSjM0xjVj88Gsxvg69L8BZ2grJNpV9bwKYXeBsBh02zv8ASp/AV7YWPAWgJKyCYWUZIO/UZ/ehXRba%2bk066kvpZCjRMgLSl1ORjIyAasbmCLS1jsobcSLbRrEp6ZwoFMrk4%2bjG7tLWCfOf6FE3Ftgj8iAkjckLtTDcSNIA1tND3Z3PMuSKEmlkLKvsyKfIAU7EXx7u%2bOozTN5HPfJNhtY3947gtLA6EjPKN8flU6SG0uEEpSDnJxkLyt%2btAS3LxAjlxnxA3pm5v5hHj2hlBOcZxijVmF5Hqax5NT4ZeNLKa6mS0tE3KRLjMS%2bHMfM0Jw3EU%2brHL2c%2bQ0jxAAvGCfdJPmd9qoZ47S/4chuLXUpoxMg5vD0w2D1BzQZc93w7Z3E1veRLzsGLKCXc53ySdzVVrg7JXLXKDbifVVdzb225LKvKoz1IA2qPcOzSSSvMJM5JONuvWhzS0fiPXliilkW1i5ZJpFJUl/wrkb7dTj0o%2bveFdVtIUkisTcxKBytbHnGPVetMrWDE7gnY08ZQOq6NIFJ3BAUjO%2bafmAgcpKoSVQCVyDj54qHc3D23MkiujDqrqQR6YNV0t/IAqhE5CSenXNM2RjSwWTyXEyMI48xjdmX8IqouDs/VlC4bm8z5VNtPYJtPuva75YLwAuniMDouPXbf1HrVdb219fX8Vrp8TPcPkKrHA26sSdqGSI4H/9k=\' /%3e%3c/svg%3e" width="512" alt="At the Beach." data-srcset="/assets/static/AtTheBog-w480.f96beb6e13d8c6a37e916755f3475e78.jpg 480w, /assets/static/AtTheBog-w512.f96beb6e13d8c6a37e916755f3475e78.jpg 512w" data-sizes="(max-width: 512px) 100vw, 512px" data-src="/assets/static/AtTheBog-w512.f96beb6e13d8c6a37e916755f3475e78.jpg"><noscript><img class="g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded" src="/assets/static/AtTheBog-w512.f96beb6e13d8c6a37e916755f3475e78.jpg" width="512" alt="At the Beach."></noscript></a>\n<em>Hey! It was overcast and windy.</em>\nBut like I said before, <a href="/blog/2018/12/02/a-little-help-from-my-friends">I get by with a little help from my friends.</a> Having a circle of friends has become important to me. Crazy, I know! I manage to organize things so I seem to get away every other weekend, doing things from LAN-ing up for some vintage Halo to going to a pub.</p>\n<p>I’m still extremely awkward, but dating is more fun than hard. It’s still not an overly frequent event, though. I have pity for <a href="/blog/2017/04/11/dating-is-hard-and-i-am-very-awkward">the version of me from years ago when that first “personal” entry was posted.</a> I don’t get nervous for most things in life now, plus I’ve learned the fine art of shutting the hell up and listening rather than raving on.</p>\n<p>Some of the time, at least.</p>\n<p>I am gaming much more. I picked up an Xbox One and opted to go all digital with games. Right now it’s showing 204 games installed, that many physical discs would require a small shed! I’m not sure of the legitimacy of the various key trading websites I’ve been using to buy stuff, but I like to live dangerously. I’m also using the Game Pass subscription service Microsoft offers. Picking up 6 month extensions as they’ve come on sale has got me all loaded up until sometime late 2020. Remember when that felt like an unobtainable future?</p>\n<p><a href="/assets/static/src/media/images/blog/XboxGameCount.jpg"><img class="g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loading" src="data:image/svg+xml,%3csvg fill=\'none\' viewBox=\'0 0 1920 1440\' xmlns=\'http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\' xmlns:xlink=\'http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink\'%3e%3cdefs%3e%3cfilter id=\'__svg-blur-76\'%3e%3cfeGaussianBlur in=\'SourceGraphic\' stdDeviation=\'40\'/%3e%3c/filter%3e%3c/defs%3e%3cimage x=\'0\' y=\'0\' filter=\'url(%23__svg-blur-76)\' width=\'1920\' height=\'1440\' xlink:href=\'data:image/jpeg%3bbase64%%2bmpbEu62gUsctxjJ%2btErC3UQkswj/AMsZxTDpsETptDxysvzEKPtVLQsDwCBUOImUflWMLdwu3d8RCjjuTim2OxhI5iT/AFWjabDtBMaFgcggdwaW0bZBPaK923iePTLa1W5AhEoRzgKectnt0pMvEnXVY4pVUSy7QzJyCuedrfxiqR7XIn0XxLFq7OhhlhWAxgHccAnr2H1qc3GtQatqIexgjgSCIBYFyq/MMkcHn%2bBTFlhLFSW1%2boCLbnrwCtfIjt5IhslIHx5%2bcDB6Gk5IoveUEbSFQwK9%2btOfi2Ge3hmmunhcyIVBjcNtX8J4zSvZwrHNaNgAMy85PrUuXjGXTwV49w7%2bTsXTlbyzsALdgTij1gsu7%2b6iKOxViT9qBWRXymDKWGOVHejGnuqY8u3lUN1OAPuarZMHYk471uyDbXriYheOT6VuXOzJGD6UDMJN7e9GfUdF08WkG%2bf3ghmHZdp61ELezutEuHiuY0VtiPsXk4JOMn1wTXTfju/mg0adLS0a4lKk7kIJjwOCR1wenFQf3ae70PWrlg9vce6SMUkBBOO49M%2btJek69fYV8FpWJXi9CbNzI3ml4yylEOFPX9waDgRP/TNihcsuFA6DPeiqWs0t/p4a2gtz5gG5XYt8p65PNbXAQvbqYlT4UUFBznv9aUm5aZRkVPSpHS1jcDDZZgMdV6j9KO2N4qrgefJ3yUP/ACkjTr1UkO5sAUettWhwu192fwgmrWyZDlBcgoDgjI6HrWSXGFPal%2bPUkK8HH5GvEuogjrS7No%2bHxSst086RXUseIQdkUasSc4zz%2bvSpxq0Ah0PWFFzdXTeU0DiTaCN2c5C9MdPSnnxDdyTWRjtwWcsM7XCkD1yanWr3Men2F/Azxbp18pWU7jJI5OAxHYZ6n1NL4qUWnJ36A7E0h02W01KFo1lkMbZXe%2bcDpnH1%2b9C5T5d5HAu5JVweSePypjvBNFcLJJLEBENxRDnjJ46etJ95eMrG5IVmySo6Ac103HlTVa%2bRqt7TP//Z\' /%3e%3c/svg%3e" width="1920" alt="Too Many Games." data-srcset="/assets/static/XboxGameCount-w480.3a98960fe11d8743a09de001e9276060.jpg 480w, /assets/static/XboxGameCount-w1024.3a98960fe11d8743a09de001e9276060.jpg 1024w, /assets/static/XboxGameCount-w1920.3a98960fe11d8743a09de001e9276060.jpg 1920w" data-sizes="(max-width: 1920px) 100vw, 1920px" data-src="/assets/static/XboxGameCount-w1920.3a98960fe11d8743a09de001e9276060.jpg"><noscript><img class="g-image g-image--lazy g-image--loaded" src="/assets/static/XboxGameCount-w1920.3a98960fe11d8743a09de001e9276060.jpg" width="1920" alt="Too Many Games."></noscript></a>\n<em>The big number is daunting.</em>\nA few highlights from the experience are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href="http://www.snake-pass.com/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Snake Pass:</a> Very frustrating until you figure out how to actually progress, but it’s such a beautiful game with a neat approach to traversal.</li>\n<li><a href="https://sniperelite4.com/en" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Sniper Elite 4:</a> Yes, it’s absolutely absurd. But it’s fun! Any bugs or annoying quirks from prior installments in the series have been ironed out. Testicle shots always cause me to wince.</li>\n<li><a href="https://www.sega.com/games/sonic-forces" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Sonic Forces:</a> An attempt to return to the tried and true method, after not being successful for a bit. It is the same Sonic Colours/Sonic Generations gameplay, oddly limited in scope despite attempts to put new features in like character creation. Not amazing, but I was still left wanting more. Maybe even <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9gc0169Ht48" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">One More Last First Bump.</a></li>\n<li><a href="https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/p/halo-5-guardians/brrc2bp0g9p0?activetab=pivot:overviewtab" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Halo 5: Guardians:</a> Extremely strong mechanics, tuned almost too well.. The story got a bit… bogged down. The removal of split screen was unfortunate, largely because none of my friends are at all interested in an Xbox One. Would love to do a 4 player team to push through on Legendary difficulty, but alas.</li>\n<li><a href="https://forzamotorsport.net/en-us/games/fh4" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">Forza Horizon 4:</a> I was impressed by realising how much tech must be under the hood in order to have all these different vehicles handle so well in so many different environments. Racing isn’t a high priority, my biggest time sink is blindly exploring this little bit of fictional Britain.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>I still have things to get to! I really want to dive into Paper Mario: Color Splash on Wii U - having that and others in my backlog is somewhat holding me back from investing in a Switch.</p>\n<p>Sometime in the New Year, when the postal service starts to run again, I should have another budget review up. This time it’s for what I’d call the cheapest viable phone. It’s from a brand I’ve never heard of, but on paper it looks like a deal. I think I’m getting hooked to the thrill of the gamble. <a href="https://youtu.be/kzwHs9PhJwY?t=99" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">I take a chance, I roll the dice</a> and either get a great deal or dog shit.</p>\n<p>Could that be a metaphor for dating? Maybe, but it’s not very kind.</p>\n',date:"2018-12-30T13:00:00+13:00",timeToRead:1}}}}}]);